projectGridLines.title: Project 1 Title: Youtube & Social Media
projectGridLines.description:
Project 1 Title: Youtube & Social Media


Description: Manage content creation, editing & co-ordinate the the shoots for

the new youtube & social projects.

Skill sets: Experience of running & own channel, Video Editing, Adobe After

Effects, Adobe Premier Pro, etc.

Expected learning: Work with key content creators, leading doctors & the

founders to run & scale the channel. Ground level experience of scaling a

business channel for user engagement & growth.

Specific courses required for project execution: None compulsory, Good to have -

Print Audio & Visual Ad, Creative Writing, Short film & video production.

projectGridLines.title: Project 2 Title: Entrepreneur In Residence
projectGridLines.description:
Project 2 Title: Entrepreneur In Residence


Description: An ideal EIR is something who wants to startup sometime soon and wants

to learn on the different facets of entrepreneurship.

As an EIR, you are expected to be a hustler who can don different hats and work on

multiple problem statements ranging from acquisition (content, referrals), retention,

monetisation working with product, design, content and engineering teams closely.

You will understand the importance of talking to users, building communication plans,

understanding business metrics, basic analytics, setting up SoPs with check mechanisms

and more.

Skill sets: Communication skills, ability to analyze consumer data & ideate solutions

Traits expectation:As an EIR, you are expected to be a hustler who can don different

hats and work on multiple problem statements ranging from acquisition (content,

referrals), retention, monetisation working with product, design, content and engineering

teams closely.

Expected learning: Work on real world product impacting lives of people internationally

& develop critical problem-solving skills, gaining experience in stakeholder management

and team collaboration.
